{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, our method is lightweight, model-agnostic, and easily deployable within existing RAG architectures.",
    "This study examined how LLM-based question decomposition (QD) and cross-encoder reranking influence retrieval-augmented generation for complex and multi-hop question answering.",
    "Across four system variants and two datasets, the combination of QD and reranking provided the largest gains, increasing retrieval and answer correctness, without requiring extra training or domain-specific tuning.",
    "Splitting a query into focused sub-queries broadened evidence coverage, while the reranker promoted the most relevant passages, yielding improvements on benchmark datasets.",
    "But the approach is not without downsides."
  ]
}